<item>
            <title>[FLINK-11400] JobManagerRunner does not wait for suspension of JobMaster</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-11400</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;JobManagerRunner&lt;/tt&gt; does not wait for the suspension of the &lt;tt&gt;JobMaster&lt;/tt&gt; to finish before granting leadership again. This can lead to a state where the &lt;tt&gt;JobMaster&lt;/tt&gt; tries to start the &lt;tt&gt;ExecutionGraph&lt;/tt&gt; but the &lt;tt&gt;SlotPool&lt;/tt&gt; is still stopped.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I suggest to linearize the leadership operations (granting and revoking leadership) similarly to the &lt;tt&gt;Dispatcher&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
